  "designNotes": {
    "endingDesign": "The lens-dependent ending is the most important design decision in Issue 12. Players choose an ending by choosing a lens — which is how they've been making meaning throughout the entire game. No menu, no dialogue tree, no explicit ending selector. The lens is the choice.",
    "allEndingsValid": "The three ending variants are all valid and complete. Locked Stability is not a bad ending. The Gutter Path is not a secret ending — it is available to careful players who engaged with the Gutter throughout.",
    "finalCaption": "Completion does not mean certainty. It means the story can continue. — Applies equally to all three endings, to the player's experience, and to the fictional universe. The thesis statement of the game.",
    "demolitionStatus": "Demolition equipment parked — the game does not confirm the demolition is cancelled. The story can continue. In a future season or never.",
    "gutterEntityFinalLine": "Season 2 tease. Not required to be built. Honest to the character.",
    "overallTone": "The longest pause in any game the player has ever played. Ceremony. Silence. The payoff for every puzzle solved, every panel restored, every glyph recovered. It should feel sacred without being solemn. Complete without being closed."
  }
}
